result.execSummary:
Jaxx J Erickson was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jaxx J Erickson was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

1:03 PM Defendant Jaxx J Erickson in court, in custody.  Attorney Alex Kitto in court for Jaxx J Erickson.  Prosecuting attorney Brady James Seidlitz in court for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant waives extradition.  Court questions Defendant.  Defendant signs Waiver of Extradition form.  Court finds waiver is knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily given.

10:11 AM Defendant Jaxx J Erickson appeared by video, in custody.  Prosecuting attorney Brady James Seidlitz in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
COVERS 22CF234 & 22CM57
Attorney Steuer relates and states Defendant needs to apply to PD office.
10:12 AM Attorney Rockow and Defendant in breakout room.
10:19 AM  Attorney Rockow and Defendant back from breakout room.
Attorney Rockow relates and Defendant qualifies for PD. 
Next hearing to be in front of Judge Bitney.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for October 19, 2022 at 10:00 am.

Defendant shall be fingerprinted at the Barron County Sheriff's Dept., if not already done.
If represented by the Public Defender and does not have a phone, must contact the Public Defender weekly at 715-908-8473. 
Must have no contact with H.D.H.

01:00 PM Defendant Jaxx J Erickson appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Alex Kitto appears for DE.  Attorney Brady Seidlitz appears for the state.  This covers cases 22CF234 & 22CM57.  Attorney Kitto relates DE should contact PD office to determine eligibility.  Warrant is quashed in 22CM57.   

22CF234 - State requests $5,000.00 cash bond. Court orders $5,000.00 cash bond and no contact with H.D.H.  

22CM57 -  State requests $250.00 cash bond.  Court orders $250.00 cash bond and no contact with H.D.H.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for October 12, 2022 at 10:00 am.
